{
  "texts": [
    "This observation reflects the improvement in the sample complexity dependence on prediction error ϵ.",
    "The sample complexity in 36 depends exponentially on 1/ϵ, but Theorem 1 establishes a quasi-polynomial dependence on 1/ϵ.",
    "From Fig. 2A (Right), we can see that the ML algorithms do not yield a substantially worse prediction error as the system size n increases.",
    "This observation matches with the logðnÞ sample complexity in Theorem 1, but not with the poly(n) sample complexity proven in 36.",
    "These improvements are also relevant when comparing the ML predictions to actual correlation function values."
  ]
}